84

91 }
92 } catch (e) {// noop

94 };</script>
95 <script>(function bootstrapTheme() {
96 // This code needs to run on legacy browsers (so ES5 only)
97 var supportsCssCustomProperties = window.CSS && window.CSS.supports && window.CSS.supports("color", "var(--test, red)");
98
99 if (!supportsCssCustomProperties) {
100 // hide content untill we can load `css-vars-ponyfill`
101 document.documentElement.classList.add("invisible");
102 } else {
103 // set CSS variables to the right value (before any rendering) to avoid a flash of inaccurate color theme
104 // eslint-disable-next-line no-inner-declarations
105 function getInitialTheme() {
106 var themeSettingName = "kae";
107 var themeSettingCookieName = "ae";
108 var themeSettingValueLight = "-1";
109 var themeSettingValueDark = "d";
110 var themeSettingValueTerminal = "t";
111 var themeKeyDark = "dark";
112 var themeKeyLight = "light"; // Helper function to get search params from URL
113
114 function getParamFromURL(url, paramName) {
115 var regex = new RegExp("[?&]" + paramName + "=([^&#]*)");
116 var match = url.match(regex);
117 return match && decodeURIComponent(match[1]);
118 } // Prioritize URL params over Cookie value
119
120
121 var param = getParamFromURL(document.URL, themeSettingName);
122
123 if (param) {
124 if (param === themeSettingValueLight) {
125 return themeKeyLight;
126 }
127
128 if (param === themeSettingValueDark || param === themeSettingValueTerminal) {
129 return themeKeyDark;
130 }
131 } // Fallback to cookie if theme setting not in URL params
132
133
134 var cookies = document.cookie.split(/; */);
135 var themeCookie;
136
137 for (var i = 0; i < cookies.length; i++) {
138 var cookie = cookies[i];
139 var re = new RegExp("^" + themeSettingCookieName + "=");
140
141 if (re.test(cookie)) {
142 themeCookie = cookie;
143 break;
144 }
145 }
146
147 if (themeCookie) {
148 var persisted = themeCookie.split("=")[1];
149
150 if (persisted === themeSettingValueLight) {
151 return themeKeyLight;
152 }
153
154 if (persisted === themeSettingValueTerminal) {
155 return themeKeyDark;
156 }
157 } // Lastly, check prefers-color-scheme setting
158
159
160 var mql = window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)");
161 return mql.matches ? themeKeyDark : themeKeyLight;
162 }

1,210 <div class="flex-grid justify-between">
1,211 <div class="flameSection_faqLeftCol__VC9Jy">
1,212 <h2 class="heading_heading2__oEFPn heading_heading__IiMSV">Still have questions?</h2>
1,213 </div>
1,214 <div class="flameSection_faqRightCol__W1Frr">
1,215 <div>
1,216 <div class="" type="single" data-reach-accordion="">
1,217 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 2px; --parent-gap-size: 2px;">
1,218 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="1" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="open">
1,219 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--0" aria-expanded="true" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="open" id="button--9--0"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">What is DuckDuckGo?</span>
1,220 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,221 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,222 </svg></button></h3>
1,223 <div role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--0" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="open" id="panel--9--0">
1,224 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo is an independent Internet privacy company that aims to make getting privacy simple and accessible for everyone. Our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/get-duckduckgo/does-duckduckgo-make-a-browser/">free web browser</a> for <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/mobile/ios">iOS</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/mobile/android">Android</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/get-duckduckgo/get-duckduckgo-browser-on-mac">Mac</a>, and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/get-duckduckgo/get-duckduckgo-browser-on-windows">Windows</a> lets you search and browse the web, but — unlike Google Search and Chrome — we don’t track your searches or browsing history, and we block other companies from trying to track you, all by default. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,225 </div>
1,226 </section>
1,227 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="2" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,228 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--1" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--1"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">How does DuckDuckGo protect my privacy?</span>
1,229 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,230 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,231 </svg></button></h3>
1,232 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--1" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--1">
1,233 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 1.5rem; --parent-gap-size: 1.5;">
1,234 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo is an independent Google alternative that also lets you search and browse the web, but we don’t track your searches or browsing history, and our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/get-duckduckgo/does-duckduckgo-make-a-browser/">browsers</a> and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/desktop/adding-duckduckgo-to-your-browser/">extensions</a> help block other companies from trying to track you as well, all by default. Our browser comes with seamless privacy protection built-in, including <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">tracker blocking</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#smarter-encryption-https-upgrading">increased encryption</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/email-protection/what-is-duckduckgo-email-protection/">Email Protection</a>, and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">more</a>. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/how-does-duckduckgo-protect-privacy/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,235 </div>
1,236 </div>
1,237 </section>
1,238 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="3" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,239 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--2" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--2"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">Does DuckDuckGo block all trackers on websites I visit?</span>
1,240 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,241 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,242 </svg></button></h3>
1,243 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--2" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--2">
1,244 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 1.5rem; --parent-gap-size: 1.5;">
1,245 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/privacy">never tracks you</a>. And when you leave our search engine and use our browsers or extensions to visit other sites, we aim to protect your privacy as much as possible. No service can eliminate all hidden tracking or all profiling online because trackers are always trying to evade specific protections. To be effective, our protections continually evolve to mitigate this while avoiding website breakage. That’s also why we offer multiple types of <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">web tracking protections</a>.</p>
1,246 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">Other browsers offer some of these by default, like cookie and fingerprinting protections, but we also provide many other protections that most browsers do not offer by default, like <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#3rd-party-tracker-loading-protection">3rd-Party Tracker Loading Protection</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#global-privacy-control-gpc">Global Privacy Control</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#link-tracking-protection">Link Tracking Protection</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#cname-cloaking-protection">CNAME Cloaking Protection</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#google-amp-protection">Google AMP Protection</a>, and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">more</a>, which all help cover different tracking angles. Our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://github.com/duckduckgo/tracker-blocklists">list of trackers</a> is open source, along with the <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://github.com/duckduckgo/privacy-configuration">list of exceptions</a> we make to preserve usability. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,247 </div>
1,248 </div>
1,249 </section>
1,250 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="4" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,251 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--3" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--3"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">How many people use DuckDuckGo?</span>
1,252 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,253 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,254 </svg></button></h3>
1,255 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--3" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--3">
1,256 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">We don’t track our users, so it’s impossible for us to know how many people in total actually use our product. However, we can make an estimate based on the number of searches we get each month. Our best guess — over 100 million people! Thanks to all these users, DuckDuckGo <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://radar.cloudflare.com/reports/searchengines-2023-q1">holds the #2 position in mobile search market share</a> in the US, and 18 other markets including Australia, Austria, Belgium, Canada, Denmark, France, Germany, Ireland, Italy, Malta, New Zealand, Poland, Portugal, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, and Switzerland.</p>
1,257 </div>
1,258 </section>
1,259 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="5" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,260 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--4" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--4"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">How does DuckDuckGo make money?</span>
1,261 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,262 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,263 </svg></button></h3>
1,264 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--4" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--4">
1,265 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">We make money from private ads on our search engine. On other search engines, ads are based on profiles compiled from your personal information, such as search, browsing, and purchase history. Since we don’t have that information per our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, search ads on DuckDuckGo are based on the search results page you’re viewing instead of being based on who other companies and their tracking algorithms assume you are as a person. For example, if you search for cars, we’ll show you ads about cars. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/how-duckduckgo-makes-money/">Learn more.</a></p>
1,266 </div>
1,267 </section>
1,268 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="6" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,269 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--5" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--5"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">Why use DuckDuckGo instead of Google?</span>
1,270 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,271 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,272 </svg></button></h3>
1,273 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--5" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--5">
1,274 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 1.5rem; --parent-gap-size: 1.5;">
1,275 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp"><b>Use DuckDuckGo to get more privacy online.</b> Ever see ads so creepy it feels like your phone is listening to you? Or notice ads following you around for something you searched for once? If you’re wondering who to blame, it’s probably Google. For decades, Google has been tracking your searches, embedding trackers in the Chrome browser, and hiding even more trackers on the most-popular websites.</p>
1,276 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">In contrast, our browser lets you search and browse like you’re used to, but (unlike Google) we never track you and our browser helps block Google’s trackers and those from other companies that operate other online tracking networks like TikTok and Meta (Facebook).</p>
1,277 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp"><b>Use DuckDuckGo to get a better online experience.</b> Have you noticed Google search results getting worse? <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2022/06/google-search-algorithm-internet/661325/">You’re not alone</a>. For many Google searches, most of the results on the first page are either ads or Google pushing their own services. It can be even worse on mobile.</p>
1,278 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">On DuckDuckGo, we keep ads to a minimum and our search ads are private, only based on the search results page you’re viewing, and not on you as a person. The tracker blocking that’s built-in to our browser also blocks a large number of tracker-dependent ads from loading by default. Coupled with other browser features like <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#cookie-pop-up-management">automatically blocking cookie pop-ups</a>, our default <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">web tracking protections</a> give you a cleaner online experience overall with DuckDuckGo.</p>
1,279 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp"><b>Use DuckDuckGo to send a message to Big Tech companies like Google who are taking away user choice online and profiting by stealing your personal information.</b> Google is the epitome of Big Tech, with their tentacles in everything, compiling detailed profiles about everyone, and making billions of dollars auctioning off access to your attention, for what? Creepy ads that follow you around? By comparison, DuckDuckGo is a small, independent company, based in Paoli, Pennsylvania, with a vision to offer a choice to be more private online without sacrifice to anyone who wants it.</p>
1,280 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">Use DuckDuckGo because it’s fast and secure, because it’s a free Google alternative that lets you search and browse the way you want, and because it puts you back in control of your personal data.</p>
1,281 </div>
1,282 </div>
1,283 </section>
1,284 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="7" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,285 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--6" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--6"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">Is Incognito mode private?</span>
1,286 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,287 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,288 </svg></button></h3>
1,289 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--6" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--6">
1,290 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">No. It is a myth that you can't be tracked while using so-called “Incognito” mode. In fact, all Incognito mode really does is delete information on your computer. Incognito mode does nothing to stop Google from saving your searches, nor does it stop companies, Internet service providers, or governments from being able to track you online. By contrast, DuckDuckGo Search never keeps your or anyone else's search history and the DuckDuckGo browser helps keep you private on websites too. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/how-does-duckduckgo-protect-privacy/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,291 </div>
1,292 </section>
1,293 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="8" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,294 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--7" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--7"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">How do DuckDuckGo Search results compare to Google's?</span>
1,295 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,296 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,297 </svg></button></h3>
1,298 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--7" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--7">
1,299 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo Search gives you truly private search results without tradeoffs in result quality. We have everything you’ve come to expect in an online search experience (images, maps, answers, etc.), and because there’s no search history on DuckDuckGo, you escape the filter bubble of manipulated results. You’ll also find <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/bangs">bonus features</a> that make our private search engine more convenient and a little more fun. We’re <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/updates">always improving</a>, so you can expect even more search improvements in the coming year! <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://spreadprivacy.com/is-duckduckgo-a-good-search-engine/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,300 </div>
1,301 </section>
1,302 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="9" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,303 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--8" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--8"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">Is DuckDuckGo owned by Google or any other entity?</span>
1,304 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,305 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,306 </svg></button></h3>
1,307 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--8" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--8">
1,308 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 1.5rem; --parent-gap-size: 1.5;">
1,309 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">No, we are not and have never been owned by Google or any other entity. We have been an independent company since our founding in 2008. We also do not source any of our search results from Google. You may notice that we offer a Google Chrome extension and a Google Android app, but these are also not in partnership with Google and actually aim to protect you from Google’s online trackers. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/how-does-duckduckgo-protect-privacy/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,310 </div>

1,351 <h2 class="footer_aboutHeading__JZ81k footer_footerHeading__CTbCv text_text-eyebrow__xZ_nL text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">About DuckDuckGo</h2>
1,352 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 2rem; --parent-gap-size: 2;">
1,353 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo is the independent Internet privacy company for anyone who’s tired of being tracked online and wants an easy solution. Unlike Chrome and other browsers, our free, go-to browser comes with over a dozen powerful privacy protections built-in, including our search engine that replaces Google and doesn't track your search history. The DuckDuckGo browser’s uniquely <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections">comprehensive privacy protections</a> are used by tens of millions of people to protect their everyday online activities, from searching to browsing, emailing, and more. Available for download on <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/mac">Mac</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/windows">Windows</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/ios">iOS</a>, and <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/android">Android</a>.</p>

82 <script>window.onerror = function _onerror(msg, source, lineno, colno) {
83 var url = "https://improving.duckduckgo.com/t/" + "static_err_global?" + Math.ceil(Math.random() * 1e7) + "&msg=" + encodeURIComponent(msg) + "&url=" + encodeURIComponent(source) + "&pathname=" + encodeURIComponent(window.location && window.location.pathname || "") + "&line=" + lineno + "&col=" + colno;
84
85 try {
86 if (window.navigator.sendBeacon) {
87 window.navigator.sendBeacon(url);
88 } else {
89 var img = document.createElement("img");
90 img.src = url;
91 }
92 } catch (e) {// noop
93 }
94 };</script>
95 <script>(function bootstrapTheme() {
96 // This code needs to run on legacy browsers (so ES5 only)
97 var supportsCssCustomProperties = window.CSS && window.CSS.supports && window.CSS.supports("color", "var(--test, red)");
98
99 if (!supportsCssCustomProperties) {
100 // hide content untill we can load `css-vars-ponyfill`
101 document.documentElement.classList.add("invisible");
102 } else {
103 // set CSS variables to the right value (before any rendering) to avoid a flash of inaccurate color theme
104 // eslint-disable-next-line no-inner-declarations
105 function getInitialTheme() {
106 var themeSettingName = "kae";
107 var themeSettingCookieName = "ae";
108 var themeSettingValueLight = "-1";
109 var themeSettingValueDark = "d";
110 var themeSettingValueTerminal = "t";
111 var themeKeyDark = "dark";
112 var themeKeyLight = "light"; // Helper function to get search params from URL
113
114 function getParamFromURL(url, paramName) {
115 var regex = new RegExp("[?&]" + paramName + "=([^&#]*)");
116 var match = url.match(regex);
117 return match && decodeURIComponent(match[1]);
118 } // Prioritize URL params over Cookie value
119
120
121 var param = getParamFromURL(document.URL, themeSettingName);
122
123 if (param) {
124 if (param === themeSettingValueLight) {
125 return themeKeyLight;
126 }
127
128 if (param === themeSettingValueDark || param === themeSettingValueTerminal) {
129 return themeKeyDark;
130 }
131 } // Fallback to cookie if theme setting not in URL params
132
133
134 var cookies = document.cookie.split(/; */);
135 var themeCookie;
136
137 for (var i = 0; i < cookies.length; i++) {
138 var cookie = cookies[i];
139 var re = new RegExp("^" + themeSettingCookieName + "=");
140
141 if (re.test(cookie)) {
142 themeCookie = cookie;
143 break;
144 }
145 }
146
147 if (themeCookie) {
148 var persisted = themeCookie.split("=")[1];
149
150 if (persisted === themeSettingValueLight) {
151 return themeKeyLight;
152 }
153
154 if (persisted === themeSettingValueTerminal) {
155 return themeKeyDark;
156 }
157 } // Lastly, check prefers-color-scheme setting
158
159
160 var mql = window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)");
161 return mql.matches ? themeKeyDark : themeKeyLight;
162 }

1,250 <div class="flameSection_faqLeftCol__VC9Jy">
1,251 <h2 class="heading_heading2__oEFPn heading_heading__IiMSV">Still have questions?</h2>
1,252 </div>
1,253 <div class="flameSection_faqRightCol__W1Frr">
1,254 <div>
1,255 <div class="" type="single" data-reach-accordion="">
1,256 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 2px; --parent-gap-size: 2px;">
1,257 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="1" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="open">
1,258 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--0" aria-expanded="true" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="open" id="button--9--0"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">What is DuckDuckGo?</span>
1,259 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,260 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,261 </svg></button></h3>
1,262 <div role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--0" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="open" id="panel--9--0">
1,263 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo is an independent Internet privacy company that aims to make getting privacy simple and accessible for everyone. Our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/get-duckduckgo/does-duckduckgo-make-a-browser/">free web browser</a> for <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/mobile/ios">iOS</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/mobile/android">Android</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/get-duckduckgo/get-duckduckgo-browser-on-mac">Mac</a>, and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/get-duckduckgo/get-duckduckgo-browser-on-windows">Windows</a> lets you search and browse the web, but — unlike Google Search and Chrome — we don’t track your searches or browsing history, and we block other companies from trying to track you, all by default. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,264 </div>
1,265 </section>
1,266 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="2" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,267 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--1" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--1"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">How does DuckDuckGo protect my privacy?</span>
1,268 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,269 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,270 </svg></button></h3>
1,271 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--1" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--1">
1,272 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 1.5rem; --parent-gap-size: 1.5;">
1,273 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo is an independent Google alternative that also lets you search and browse the web, but we don’t track your searches or browsing history, and our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/get-duckduckgo/does-duckduckgo-make-a-browser/">browsers</a> and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/desktop/adding-duckduckgo-to-your-browser/">extensions</a> help block other companies from trying to track you as well, all by default. Our browser comes with seamless privacy protection built-in, including <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">tracker blocking</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#smarter-encryption-https-upgrading">increased encryption</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/email-protection/what-is-duckduckgo-email-protection/">Email Protection</a>, and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">more</a>. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/how-does-duckduckgo-protect-privacy/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,274 </div>
1,275 </div>
1,276 </section>
1,277 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="3" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,278 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--2" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--2"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">Does DuckDuckGo block all trackers on websites I visit?</span>
1,279 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,280 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,281 </svg></button></h3>
1,282 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--2" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--2">
1,283 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 1.5rem; --parent-gap-size: 1.5;">
1,284 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/privacy">never tracks you</a>. And when you leave our search engine and use our browsers or extensions to visit other sites, we aim to protect your privacy as much as possible. No service can eliminate all hidden tracking or all profiling online because trackers are always trying to evade specific protections. To be effective, our protections continually evolve to mitigate this while avoiding website breakage. That’s also why we offer multiple types of <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">web tracking protections</a>.</p>
1,285 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">Other browsers offer some of these by default, like cookie and fingerprinting protections, but we also provide many other protections that most browsers do not offer by default, like <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#3rd-party-tracker-loading-protection">3rd-Party Tracker Loading Protection</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#global-privacy-control-gpc">Global Privacy Control</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#link-tracking-protection">Link Tracking Protection</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#cname-cloaking-protection">CNAME Cloaking Protection</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#google-amp-protection">Google AMP Protection</a>, and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">more</a>, which all help cover different tracking angles. Our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://github.com/duckduckgo/tracker-blocklists">list of trackers</a> is open source, along with the <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://github.com/duckduckgo/privacy-configuration">list of exceptions</a> we make to preserve usability. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,286 </div>
1,287 </div>
1,288 </section>
1,289 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="4" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,290 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--3" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--3"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">How many people use DuckDuckGo?</span>
1,291 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,292 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,293 </svg></button></h3>
1,294 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--3" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--3">
1,295 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">We don’t track our users, so it’s impossible for us to know how many people in total actually use our product. However, we can make an estimate based on the number of searches we get each month. Our best guess — over 100 million people! Thanks to all these users, DuckDuckGo <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://radar.cloudflare.com/reports/searchengines-2023-q1">holds the #2 position in mobile search market share</a> in the US, and 18 other markets including Australia, Austria, Belgium, Canada, Denmark, France, Germany, Ireland, Italy, Malta, New Zealand, Poland, Portugal, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, and Switzerland.</p>
1,296 </div>
1,297 </section>
1,298 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="5" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,299 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--4" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--4"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">How does DuckDuckGo make money?</span>
1,300 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,301 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,302 </svg></button></h3>
1,303 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--4" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--4">
1,304 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">We make money from private ads on our search engine. On other search engines, ads are based on profiles compiled from your personal information, such as search, browsing, and purchase history. Since we don’t have that information per our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, search ads on DuckDuckGo are based on the search results page you’re viewing instead of being based on who other companies and their tracking algorithms assume you are as a person. For example, if you search for cars, we’ll show you ads about cars. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/how-duckduckgo-makes-money/">Learn more.</a></p>
1,305 </div>
1,306 </section>
1,307 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="6" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,308 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--5" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--5"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">Why use DuckDuckGo instead of Google?</span>
1,309 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,310 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,311 </svg></button></h3>
1,312 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--5" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--5">
1,313 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 1.5rem; --parent-gap-size: 1.5;">
1,314 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp"><b>Use DuckDuckGo to get more privacy online.</b> Ever see ads so creepy it feels like your phone is listening to you? Or notice ads following you around for something you searched for once? If you’re wondering who to blame, it’s probably Google. For decades, Google has been tracking your searches, embedding trackers in the Chrome browser, and hiding even more trackers on the most-popular websites.</p>
1,315 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">In contrast, our browser lets you search and browse like you’re used to, but (unlike Google) we never track you and our browser helps block Google’s trackers and those from other companies that operate other online tracking networks like TikTok and Meta (Facebook).</p>
1,316 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp"><b>Use DuckDuckGo to get a better online experience.</b> Have you noticed Google search results getting worse? <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2022/06/google-search-algorithm-internet/661325/">You’re not alone</a>. For many Google searches, most of the results on the first page are either ads or Google pushing their own services. It can be even worse on mobile.</p>
1,317 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">On DuckDuckGo, we keep ads to a minimum and our search ads are private, only based on the search results page you’re viewing, and not on you as a person. The tracker blocking that’s built-in to our browser also blocks a large number of tracker-dependent ads from loading by default. Coupled with other browser features like <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/#cookie-pop-up-management">automatically blocking cookie pop-ups</a>, our default <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections/">web tracking protections</a> give you a cleaner online experience overall with DuckDuckGo.</p>
1,318 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp"><b>Use DuckDuckGo to send a message to Big Tech companies like Google who are taking away user choice online and profiting by stealing your personal information.</b> Google is the epitome of Big Tech, with their tentacles in everything, compiling detailed profiles about everyone, and making billions of dollars auctioning off access to your attention, for what? Creepy ads that follow you around? By comparison, DuckDuckGo is a small, independent company, based in Paoli, Pennsylvania, with a vision to offer a choice to be more private online without sacrifice to anyone who wants it.</p>
1,319 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">Use DuckDuckGo because it’s fast and secure, because it’s a free Google alternative that lets you search and browse the way you want, and because it puts you back in control of your personal data.</p>
1,320 </div>
1,321 </div>
1,322 </section>
1,323 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="7" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,324 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--6" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--6"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">Is Incognito mode private?</span>
1,325 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,326 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,327 </svg></button></h3>
1,328 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--6" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--6">
1,329 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">No. It is a myth that you can't be tracked while using so-called “Incognito” mode. In fact, all Incognito mode really does is delete information on your computer. Incognito mode does nothing to stop Google from saving your searches, nor does it stop companies, Internet service providers, or governments from being able to track you online. By contrast, DuckDuckGo Search never keeps your or anyone else's search history and the DuckDuckGo browser helps keep you private on websites too. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/how-does-duckduckgo-protect-privacy/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,330 </div>
1,331 </section>
1,332 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="8" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,333 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--7" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--7"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">How do DuckDuckGo Search results compare to Google's?</span>
1,334 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,335 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,336 </svg></button></h3>
1,337 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--7" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--7">
1,338 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo Search gives you truly private search results without tradeoffs in result quality. We have everything you’ve come to expect in an online search experience (images, maps, answers, etc.), and because there’s no search history on DuckDuckGo, you escape the filter bubble of manipulated results. You’ll also find <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/bangs">bonus features</a> that make our private search engine more convenient and a little more fun. We’re <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/updates">always improving</a>, so you can expect even more search improvements in the coming year! <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://spreadprivacy.com/is-duckduckgo-a-good-search-engine/">Learn more</a>.</p>
1,339 </div>
1,340 </section>
1,341 <section class="accordion_accordionItem__im5rc" value="9" data-reach-accordion-item="" data-state="collapsed">
1,342 <h3 class="accordion_accordionHeader__C77Sy"><button aria-controls="panel--9--8" aria-expanded="false" class="accordion_accordionTrigger__WmvuX" data-reach-accordion-button="" data-state="collapsed" id="button--9--8"><span class="heading_heading5__s_WB9 heading_heading__IiMSV heading_responsive__oZpJJ">Is DuckDuckGo owned by Google or any other entity?</span>
1,343 <svg viewbox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion_accordionTriggerIcon__P9sgZ" aria-hidden="true">
1,344 <path d="M13.5 5.5L8 11 2.5 5.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
1,345 </svg></button></h3>
1,346 <div hidden role="region" aria-labelledby="button--9--8" class="accordion_accordionContent__fzXEY" data-reach-accordion-panel="" data-state="collapsed" id="panel--9--8">
1,347 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 1.5rem; --parent-gap-size: 1.5;">
1,348 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">No, we are not and have never been owned by Google or any other entity. We have been an independent company since our founding in 2008. We also do not source any of our search results from Google. You may notice that we offer a Google Chrome extension and a Google Android app, but these are also not in partnership with Google and actually aim to protect you from Google’s online trackers. <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/company/how-does-duckduckgo-protect-privacy/">Learn more</a>.</p>

1,390 <h2 class="footer_aboutHeading__JZ81k footer_footerHeading__CTbCv text_text-eyebrow__xZ_nL text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">About DuckDuckGo</h2>
1,391 <div class="stack_root__Mp7Le" style="--gap-size: 2rem; --parent-gap-size: 2;">
1,392 <p class="text_text-sm__23qqs text_text__q9rvO text_responsive__9czhp">DuckDuckGo is the independent Internet privacy company for anyone who’s tired of being tracked online and wants an easy solution. Unlike Chrome and other browsers, our free, go-to browser comes with over a dozen powerful privacy protections built-in, including our search engine that replaces Google and doesn't track your search history. The DuckDuckGo browser’s uniquely <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/privacy/web-tracking-protections">comprehensive privacy protections</a> are used by tens of millions of people to protect their everyday online activities, from searching to browsing, emailing, and more. Available for download on <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/mac">Mac</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/windows">Windows</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/ios">iOS</a>, and <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer_footerLink__SlwES" href="https://duckduckgo.com/android">Android</a>.</p>

233 <h2 class="LnpumSThxEWMIsDdAT17 CXMyPcQ6nDv47DKFeywM"><a href="https://www.selenium.dev/" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-testid="result-title-a" data-handled-by-react="true" class="eVNpHGjtxRBq_gLOfGDr LQNqh2U1kzYxREs65IJu"><span class="EKtkFWMYpwzMKOYr0GYm LQVY1Jpkk8nyJ6HBWKAk">Selenium</span></a></h2>
234 </div>
235 <div class="E2eLOJr8HctVnDOTM8fs">
236 <div data-result="snippet" class="OgdwYG6KE2qthn9XQWFC">
237 <span class="kY2IgmnCmOGjharHErah" style="-webkit-line-clamp: 3;"><span><b>Selenium</b> is a project that provides tools for automating web applications and browser tasks, such as testing, debugging, and administration. Learn how to use <b>Selenium</b> WebDriver, IDE, Grid, and Level to create robust and scalable automation suites and scripts.</span></span>
238 </div>

240 <div class="FTrf7TqAcfxxEQ_3nfUg">
241 <div class="nYs5EPJFwdhisN0E7MCB AbEGLIJuTmsLLjCjXvCN">
242 <ul class="b269SZlC2oyR13Fcc4Iy">
243 <li id="sl-0" class="gyDT4qronqJu4BgQBq2F"><a href="https://www.selenium.dev/downloads" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-handled-by-react="true" class="f3uDrYrWF3Exrfp1m3Og"><h3 class="EKtkFWMYpwzMKOYr0GYm LQVY1Jpkk8nyJ6HBWKAk">Downloads</h3></a><p class="KoEJ3YBbjXKVOE1bc2RA"><span class="kY2IgmnCmOGjharHErah" style="-webkit-line-clamp: 2;">In order to create scripts that interact with the Selenium Server (Remote WebDriver) or create local Selenium WebDriver scripts, you need to make use of language-specific client drivers. While language bindings for other languages exist, these are the core ones that are supported by the main project hosted on GitHub. C#.</span></p></li>
244 <li id="sl-1" class="gyDT4qronqJu4BgQBq2F"><a href="https://selenium.dev/selenium-ide/" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-handled-by-react="true" class="f3uDrYrWF3Exrfp1m3Og"><h3 class="EKtkFWMYpwzMKOYr0GYm LQVY1Jpkk8nyJ6HBWKAk">Selenium Ide</h3></a><p class="KoEJ3YBbjXKVOE1bc2RA"><span class="kY2IgmnCmOGjharHErah" style="-webkit-line-clamp: 2;">Selenium IDE can be extended through the use of plugins. They can introduce new commands to the IDE or integrate with a third-party service. Write your own or install one that someone else has already written. Try it out. Download Selenium IDE for either Chrome or Firefox and get started.</span></p></li>
245 <li id="sl-2" class="gyDT4qronqJu4BgQBq2F"><a href="https://www.selenium.dev/sponsors" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-handled-by-react="true" class="f3uDrYrWF3Exrfp1m3Og"><h3 class="EKtkFWMYpwzMKOYr0GYm LQVY1Jpkk8nyJ6HBWKAk">Sponsors</h3></a><p class="KoEJ3YBbjXKVOE1bc2RA"><span class="kY2IgmnCmOGjharHErah" style="-webkit-line-clamp: 2;">The following companies have sponsored the Selenium project. Would you like your company to be listed on this page?</span></p></li>
246 <li id="sl-3" class="gyDT4qronqJu4BgQBq2F"><a href="https://www.selenium.dev/about" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-handled-by-react="true" class="f3uDrYrWF3Exrfp1m3Og"><h3 class="EKtkFWMYpwzMKOYr0GYm LQVY1Jpkk8nyJ6HBWKAk">About</h3></a><p class="KoEJ3YBbjXKVOE1bc2RA"><span class="kY2IgmnCmOGjharHErah" style="-webkit-line-clamp: 2;">The Selenium project is a member of the Software Freedom Conservancy, a 501(c)3 non-profit organization. The Conservancy has reduced the management overhead associated with creating our own, dedicated legal entity. The majority of sponsorship funds go directly towards supporting the Selenium project, such as server, software and conference ...</span></p></li>
247 <li id="sl-4" class="gyDT4qronqJu4BgQBq2F"><a href="https://www.selenium.dev/documentation" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-handled-by-react="true" class="f3uDrYrWF3Exrfp1m3Og"><h3 class="EKtkFWMYpwzMKOYr0GYm LQVY1Jpkk8nyJ6HBWKAk">Documentation</h3></a><p class="KoEJ3YBbjXKVOE1bc2RA"><span class="kY2IgmnCmOGjharHErah" style="-webkit-line-clamp: 2;">Selenium Manager (Beta) Selenium Manager is a command-line tool implemented in Rust that provides automated driver and browser management for Selenium. Selenium bindings use this tool by default, so you do not need to download it or add anything to your code or do anything else to use it.</span></p></li>
248 <li id="sl-5" class="gyDT4qronqJu4BgQBq2F"><a href="https://www.selenium.dev/projects" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-handled-by-react="true" class="f3uDrYrWF3Exrfp1m3Og"><h3 class="EKtkFWMYpwzMKOYr0GYm LQVY1Jpkk8nyJ6HBWKAk">Projects</h3></a><p class="KoEJ3YBbjXKVOE1bc2RA"><span class="kY2IgmnCmOGjharHErah" style="-webkit-line-clamp: 2;">Selenium has many projects that combine to form a versatile testing system. Selenium WebDriver. Selenium WebDriver drives a browser natively, as a real user would, either locally or on remote machines. Simple and concise. WebDriver is simple, it is designed as a concise and compact programming interface.</span></p></li>

424 <div data-hide-untill-css-vars-polyfilled="true" data-react-module-id="about" class="react-module">
425 <div class="wbUB0U7KMDyukXtzMd8Y NCwWYRkAos7ntUjEoEWk">
426 <div data-testid="about" class="O9Ipab51rBntYb0pwOQn zBanFIEymeySULdnPIUg rQDEM92MBDaTm3ecgrhS fs31xOJE8LUqjMg7Uhph">

428 <div class="Cwg3TAWR68fVkDBMYLUZ">
429 <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selenium" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-handled-by-react="true" class="aE0gc0ID62YmIzSXoXG2"><h2 class="Ee2e63EzQ9F3xq9wsGDY">Selenium</h2></a>
430 <div class="G6_uX_rrNQC1nVpOSuOQ">
431 <div class="aSBdOftk9efiVV8GwLLE">
432 <span>Chemical element with symbol Se and atomic number 34</span>
433 </div>
434 </div>
435 <p class="EwBVRZ62P2JekkbusBsm wZ4JdaHxSAhGy1HoNVja cPy9QU4brI7VQXFNPEvF"><span class="expandableItem">Selenium is a chemical element; it has symbol Se and atomic number 34. </span><span class="expandableItem">It is a nonmetal with properties that are intermediate between the elements above and below in the periodic table, sulfur and tellurium, and also has similarities to arsenic. </span><span class="expandableItem cTiskhpeDx_WOR3fREqC">It seldom occurs in its elemental state or as pure ore compounds in Earth's crust. </span><span class="expandableItem cTiskhpeDx_WOR3fREqC">Selenium was discovered in 1817 by Jöns Jacob Berzelius, who noted the similarity of the new element to the previously discovered tellurium. </span><span class="expandableItem cTiskhpeDx_WOR3fREqC">Selenium is found in metal sulfide ores, where it partially replaces the sulfur. </span><span class="expandableItem cTiskhpeDx_WOR3fREqC">Commercially, selenium is produced as a byproduct in the refining of these ores, most often during production. </span><span class="expandableItem cTiskhpeDx_WOR3fREqC">Minerals that are pure selenide or selenate compounds are known but rare. </span><span class="expandableItem cTiskhpeDx_WOR3fREqC">The chief commercial uses for selenium today are glassmaking and pigments. </span><span class="expandableItem cTiskhpeDx_WOR3fREqC">Selenium is a semiconductor and is used in photocells. </span><span class="expandableItem cTiskhpeDx_WOR3fREqC">Applications in electronics, once important, have been mostly replaced with silicon semiconductor devices.</span> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selenium" rel="noopener" target="_self" data-handled-by-react="true" class="JhFQAeU7IMxZaS7jCOQm Bl3t3iYRHX9BeMH_V52u">Wikipedia</a></p>
436 </div>
437 <table data-testid="about-infobox" class="gs6c2145IBVttlZ1kikD">
